{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9080d8f7-97a9-4878-966e-41d601bf1f4d","content":"On macOS, when a NativeAOT app crashes, look for **Apple crash reports** in:\n\n```\n~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n```\n\nFiles are named like `YourApp_<date>_<machine>.ips` (or `.crash` on older macOS). They contain the stack trace, signal info, and loaded images.\n\n**Other options:**\n\n- **`lldb`** — attach post-mortem or run under it: `lldb ./YourApp`\n- **Console.app** — browse crash reports under *Diagnostic Reports*\n- **Core dumps** — enable with `ulimit -c unlimited` *before* running. Cores land in `/cores/` (requires SIP adjustment on modern macOS)\n\nThe `.ips` crash report is usually the quickest path when `createdump` isn't available.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"219832b1-098b-4055-9d30-ca4ac5bd6c25","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, without `createdump`. This is a general knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":256,"requestId":"CB00:392B11:6E0BE4:7E32D7:6A052983"},"id":"246b2730-8911-4a61-a3c8-7794606dbbbf","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:46:51.009Z","parentId":"bd8eb777-5627-4eff-bbc3-ebc038767b22"}
